definitions.definition: A lively dance originating in Scotland .
The music of this dance; often called a Scottish (or Scotch) reel.
A kind of spool , turning on an axis , on which yarn , threads , lines , or the like, are wound .
examples: A hose reel forms part of a hose trolley or hose cart

definitions.definition: A device consisting of radial arms with horizontal stats , connected with a harvesting machine, for holding the stalks of grain in position to be cut by the knives.
A short compilation of sample film work used as a demonstrative resume in the entertainment industry.
A chronological collection of pictures or short videos published by a user on an app or website and typically only available for a short period.
